# ddrs — DDR5 timings reader for AMD AM5

## Project structure

| Path | Language | License | Description |
|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| `src/` | Rust (edition 2024) | Apache-2.0 | Userspace CLI binary |

### Rust modules

- `main.rs` — CLI entry point (clap), backend selection, orchestration
- `smn.rs` — `SmnReader` trait and two backends: `RyzenSmuReader` (ryzen_smu sysfs) and `SysfsPciReader` (sysfs pread/pwrite)
- `channels.rs` — UMC channel probing, rank detection, capacity calculation, DMI matching
- `timings.rs` — DDR5 register map and timing extraction from SMN registers
- `smu.rs` — PM table version-dependent parsing for MCLK/FCLK/UCLK
- `dmi.rs` — SMBIOS Type 17 parsing from `/sys/firmware/dmi/entries/17-*/raw`
- `display.rs` — Terminal output formatting

### ryzen_smu sysfs interface

Uses [ryzen_smu](https://github.com/amkillam/ryzen_smu) at `/sys/kernel/ryzen_smu_drv/`:

- `smn` — write 4 bytes (address) to read, read 4 bytes for result; write 8 bytes (addr+value) to write
- `pm_table`, `pm_table_version`, `pm_table_size` — PM table for clock frequencies

## Key technical details

- SMN registers: accessed via PCI config offset 0xC4 (address) / 0xC8 (data) on AMD host bridge (0000:00:00.0)
- UMC channels: offset = `channel_index << 20`, timing registers at `0x50xxx` within each channel
- SMU mailbox: handled by ryzen_smu kernel module; RSMU registers for commands/responses
- PM table: ryzen_smu reads from physical DRAM and exposes via sysfs; userspace parses version-dependent clock offsets
- SMBIOS: Type 17 records matched to UMC DIMMs in enumeration order

## Reference projects

Register maps, SMU commands, and PM table offsets are derived from:
- [ZenTimings](https://github.com/irusanov/ZenTimings) — `DDR5Dictionary.cs`, `Ddr5Timings.cs`
- [ZenStates-Core](https://github.com/irusanov/ZenStates-Core) — `SMU.cs`, `MemoryConfig.cs`, `Zen4Settings.cs`, `Zen5Settings.cs`

## Conventions

- All Rust source files carry `// Copyright 2026 Jean-Francois Roy` + `// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0`
- Kernel module files carry `// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0-only`
- Error handling: `anyhow::Result` throughout userspace; kernel module returns negative errno
- DKMS config is at `kernel/dkms.conf`
